Source: Keralanext online, Sat Feb 2003 [edited]
<http://www.keralanext.com/news/index.asp?id=7550>

India: Increase in Number of Dengue Cases in Kochi
--------------------------------------------------
The district-level expert committee that met under Johnson K. George, ADM,
at the Collectorate here, has cautioned all sections of the public against
epidemic outbreaks. It was decided at the meeting to include the Kochi
Corporation health officer in the expert committee that already includes
district officers from the departments of panchayat, education, and water
authorities, and also to request the Kochi Mayor to instruct health
officials under the Corporation to concentrate on works related to checking
the spreading of epidemics.
The number of Dengue fever cases had risen to 71 this year from 25 cases
last year, and the chances of fatality were greater on repeated infection,
said V. K. Krishnankutty, Deputy District Medical Officer in charge of
contagious diseases. The meeting also decided to form a squad of 5 members
for every 50 houses in wards of village panchayat and councils in the
corporation to make door-to-door visits and destroy potential mosquito
breeding points.
